  "description": "Cambium: a lateral meristem — a thin, active layer of cells responsible for secondary (lateral) growth, the process by which stems and roots increase in diameter. A cambium is a perpetually juvenile tissue that remains meristematic throughout the plant's life, continuously dividing to produce new secondary xylem and phloem.",
